
[1]treachery

   TREACHERY, n. trech'ery. Violation of allegiance or of faith and
   confidence. The man who betrays his country in any manner, violates his
   allegiance, and is guilty of treachery. This is treason. The man who
   violates his faith pledged to his friend, or betrays a trust in which a
   promise of fidelity is implied, is guilty of treachery. The disclosure
   of a secret committed to one in confidence, is treachery. This is
   perfidy.
